review_blob: The best milk stout I have ever had.  Incredibly creamy in my mouth.  Worth drinking for the texture alone. Caramel, chocolate, nuts
Pours a dark burnt toasty head.  Carmel, coffee, roasty malt.  Coconut is not overbearing and gives a very smooth quality.
The best ipa in Colorado.  A perfect blend of hops with the cascade not being too strong.  Very drinkable.
One of my favorite staple beers.  Malty carmel .  Never overbearing.  Drinks like a lighter beer than it is.
